The paper discusses generative statistical models for music processing, which involves analyzing and generating chord sequences. This falls under the sub-category of "Sound and Music Computing" (cs.SD). The paper also discusses hidden Markov models and probabilistic context-free grammar models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The unsupervised learning techniques for inducing latent grammar from data also falls under the sub-category of "Statistical Learning" (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for chord categories in harmony models, which falls under the sub-category of "Computational Linguistics" (cs.CL).
